sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Gilead Sciences, Inc. (Symbol: GILD), where a total volume of 38,773 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.9 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 44.3% of GILD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 8.8 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $77 strike call option expiring November 18, 2016 , with 5,577 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 557,700 underlying shares of GILD.

JPMorgan Chase & Co (Symbol: JPM) saw options trading volume of 67,026 contracts, representing approximately 6.7 million underlying shares or approximately 44.2% of JPM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 15.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $75 strike call option expiring December 16, 2016 , with 5,082 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 508,200 underlying shares of JPM.

Below is a chart showing JPM's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $75 strike highlighted in orange:

And Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) saw options trading volume of 20,737 contracts, representing approximately 2.1 million underlying shares or approximately 43.7% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.7 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $122 strike put option expiring October 28, 2016 , with 2,635 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 263,500 underlying shares of HD.
